{"履修期": "秋学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "<div>本講義では学生が英語でコミュニケーションを取るための基本的な日常会話の語彙・文 法を修得することと、話す(発表する)技術の向上を目的としている。</div>", "到達目標": "See below", "特記事項": "【合併】英語Iｄ　６（経済学部）/英語IIｂ　６（経済学部）", "関連科目": "", "授業の概要・背景": "", "授業方法": "<div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><div>Lecture:&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Faculty members explain the details of knowledge. Basically, the main learning activity for students is to take notes of the explanations made by faculty members and from videos of Academic talks. However, these are followed by question-and-answer sessions between faculty members and students.</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Writing: Students perform ten</span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">&nbsp;Free Writing exercises (10 minutes, no dictionary required) in-class using the LUNA LMS. Students write about a wide range of interesting topics and after submission, they read and comment on their classmates’ writing.</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Pair work:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Students perform learning activities in pairs such as discussion, dictation, and peer feedback and evaluation.</span></div></div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><br /></div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Group work:&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Students make groups of three members or more to perform learning activities such as discussion, surveying, and interviewing.</span></div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><br /></div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Presentation: S</span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">tudents summarize the results of their own learning activities and present them to a partner; first an in-class rehearsals, and then students select a topic for&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">a short Poster Presentation. Each semester has two Poster Presentations in Sessions 5 &amp; 13.</span></div><div><br /></div><div>Assessment:<span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">&nbsp;Session 6 is the Mid-term test and Session 14 is the End-of-term test. Students read passages and questions related to the covered textbook units and choose from multiple choice answers. Students also write a 100-word mini-presentation script. The test&nbsp;<strong style=\"font-size:11.0224px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">does not</span></strong>&nbsp;require speaking or listening.</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Assignment for next Session preparation - Students</span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">&nbsp;prepare for the next class by reviewing the textbook’s covered content, previewing upcoming contents, and completing assigned o</span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">nline LMS homework: After registering with t</span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">he ABAX LMS Talking Point 1 website</span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">, students</span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">&nbsp;complete</span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">&nbsp;Vocabulary Matching or Recorded Speaking tasks.</span></div></div>", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">&lt;Face-to-face class&gt;</span><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">[Orientation]</div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Syllabus check, Summer Vacation<span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">&nbsp;speaking activity.</span></div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><br /></span></div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">[Writing]</div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Free Writing F1</div></span></div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><br /></span></div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Theme: Unit 6 - Nation Building</span></div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">[Lecture / Pair Work]</span></